**Subcommand Categories:**
- `jd snap` - All snapshot operations
- `jd config` - System configuration management  
- `jd sys` - System validation and testing
- `jd git` - Git workflow integration
- `jd vm` - If you add VM tooling later

**Development Workflow Integration:**
```bash
jd dev start graphics           # Create baseline, checkout branch
jd dev test ./install-gpu.sh    # Snapshot, test, prompt keep/rollback
jd dev commit "working nvidia"  # Git commit + success snapshot
jd dev reset                    # Rollback + git reset
```

**Smart Defaults:**
```bash
jd                              # Show status (recent snapshots, git branch, system health)
jd test                         # Quick system validation
jd save                         # Smart snapshot with auto-description
jd back                         # Safe rollback with confirmation
```

**Configuration:**
- `~/.config/jd/config` - Your preferences and defaults
- Plugin system for adding new tools
- Tab completion for all subcommands

